text:
Elena Hrenova (14 January 1950 – 22 November 2020) was a Moldovan politician. From 2014 to 2019 she was a Member of the Moldovan Parliament representing the Party of Socialists of the Republic of Moldova (PSRM).
On 22 November 2020, Hrenova died of COVID-19 at the age of 70.
